The paper deals with a robot that must autonomously decide where to go to collect new and scientifically relevant images given a limited ability to communicate with its human operator. This involves designing observation models, reward models, and communication strategies for the robot. The paper also introduces a novel active reward learning strategy based on making queries to help the robot minimize path ""regret"" online. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is robotics (cs.RO), followed by computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and systems and control (cs.SY).
